The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Gavaskar bats for Twenty20
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Gavaskar bats for Twenty20
                      
	Mumbai: Sunil Gavaskar feels that Twenty20 cricket is the ideal way to spread the game to countries not well-versed in it as it gets over in three hours unlike the longer versions of the game.         
	Its a terrific for the emerging nations. It gets over in three hours. This form of the game can be taken to China, the US and parts of Europe. But the important factor is the preparation of wickets, the former India captain said on the sidelines of the launch of Mumbai Indians on Thursday.         
	No regrets, he said when queried whether he wished this format was in vogue during his playing days.           (PTI)                                                                                                                      
